Thanks, Simon and Uwe, for your inputs.

It's not that TMB requires a particular version of Matrix, it just 
suggests using the same version of Matrix as it was built with. We may 
have seen this problem before, with innocuous changes in Rcpp breaking 
downstream packages.

A different example, running in two separate sessions for comparison, is 
shown below.

Windows may be rebuilding more often than strictly necessary, but it 
seems the right thing to do to me. We could assess the overhead using 
historic data to see how big of an impact that would be.

I hear you're proposing that the TMB maintainers release an updated 
version whenever Matrix is updated?


Best regards

Kirill


